-- Monsoon Rainfall in India 38% Above Normal Last Week, Weather Bureau Says
-- Thomas Kutty Abraham
-- 2010-07-29T08:06:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-29/monsoon-rainfall-in-india-38-above-normal-last-week-weather-bureau-says.html

          
          
             India’s monsoon, the main source of
irrigation for the nation’s 235 million farmers, was 38 percent
above average last week, the weather office said.  
 The nation received 94.3 millimeters of rain in the week
ended July 28, more than than the 50-year average of 68.2
millimeters for the period, according to the India
Meteorological Department. Monsoon is 5 percent below normal
since the season began on June 1, it said.  
          
          


  


        